    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1968-10-16T06:26:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1968-10-16T06:26:00-05:00" n="78"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d78">
                <head>78. Telegram From the <gloss type="from">Department of State</gloss> to the
                        <gloss type="to">Embassy in France</gloss>
                    <note n="1" type="source" xml:id="d78fn1">Source: National Archives and Records
                        Administration, <gloss target="#t_RG1">RG</gloss> 59, <gloss
                            target="#t_AIM1">A/IM</gloss> Files: Lot 93 D 82, <gloss
                            target="#t_HARVAN1">HARVAN</gloss>-(Outgoing)-October 1968. Secret;
                        Immediate; <gloss target="#t_Nodis1">Nodis</gloss>; <gloss
                            target="#t_HARVAN1">HARVAN</gloss>/Double Plus. Drafted by <persName
                            corresp="#p_RBH1">Read</persName> and <persName corresp="#p_Bundy1"
                            >Bundy</persName>, cleared by <persName corresp="#p_CCM1"
                            >Clifford</persName> and <persName corresp="#p_RBH1">Read</persName>,
                        and approved by <persName corresp="#p_RD1">Rusk</persName>.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>Washington</placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian"
                            when="1968-10-16T11:26:00+00:00">October 16, 1968,
                        1126Z</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>256008/<gloss target="#t_Todel1">Todel</gloss> 1284. For <persName
                        corresp="#p_HWA1">Harriman</persName> and <persName corresp="#p_VCR1"
                        >Vance</persName>. Deliver at Opening of Business.</p>
                <list>
                    <label>1.</label>
                    <item>At the teabreak tomorrow you should tell <persName corresp="#p_XTC1"
                            >Thuy</persName> or hand him a note, if you think that preferable for
                        security or other reasons, indicating: (1) We have no intention of stopping
                        the bombing until the <gloss target="#t_DRV1">DRV</gloss> is willing to give
                        us a date on which we can begin serious talks with <gloss target="#t_GVN1"
                            >GVN</gloss> representatives present; (2) The <gloss target="#t_DRV1"
                            >DRV</gloss> has repeatedly indicated that serious talks could begin the
                        day after cessation and when the <gloss target="#t_DRV1">DRV</gloss> advises
                        us of the date on which such talks can start we are prepared to stop the
                        bombing the day before those talks in accordance with our presentation of
                        October 15;<note n="2" xml:id="d78fn2">See <ref target="#d71">Document
                                71</ref>.</note> (3) We see no reason for further delay and urge
                        proceeding soonest even though it may mean starting with temporary <gloss
                            target="#t_GVN1">GVN</gloss> and <gloss target="#t_NLF1">NLF</gloss>
                        representatives who could be made available promptly and then be replaced by
                        other representatives on their arrival. <gloss target="#t_FYI1">FYI</gloss>:
                        From our point of view the presence of “warm bodies” at the table the day
                        following cessation is important as a symbol and it does not matter if they
                        are soon thereafter replaced by permanent representatives. End <gloss
                            target="#t_FYI1">FYI</gloss>.</item>
                    <label>2.</label>
                    <item>As we have emphasized in our separate cable to Saigon,<note n="3"
                            xml:id="d78fn3">
                            <ref target="#d79">Document 79</ref>.</note> any delay will of course
                        create a really serious hazard of leak. We know that you will be doing
                        everything possible to handle this at your end, as we shall here.</item>
                </list>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_RD1">
                            <hi rend="strong">Rusk</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
